metadata.name: FREE UZI #01
metadata.description:
1500x1500. 60fps. 15 secs.

Edition 1 of 1.

"Created on August 2018 in Hartford, CT, B. Flores aka ‘BRYSMADWORLD’ shot a portrait that not only became a viral sensation but also a piece of rap history. What began as a traditional backstage photo at the Endless Summer Tour, turned into a photo that served as Lil Uzi Vert’s comeback avatar since announcing his “retirement” and rebellion towards Atlantic Records. Not only was this portrait used as an updated Spotify photo, but lived on Lil Uzi’s Instagram feed, and shortly after became the artwork for the now iconic “Free Uzi” track, a “leaked” song released on March 28, 2019, during Lil Uzi’s holdout from Atlantic Records."

BONUS CONTENT:

Buyer will receive the following:

* Access to original photo in it’s full resolution
* Access to additional photo that was taken on the day of.
* Access to view a scan of the film negative
* Large print of portrait (or any size desired + framed)
